Package: NewLazy
Type: Package
Title: This packages solves consumer's utility maximization problems
Version: 1.0
Date: 2016-12-02
Author: P. BOUCHE ; J. SORIN
Maintainer: paul.bouche@sciencespo.fr
Maintainer: Paul Bouche <paul.bouche@sciencespo.fr>
Description: This package aims at solving consumer's utility maximization problems for given prices, income, and utility function. It works for Cobb Douglas functions. It also outputs a corresponding graph. #' Example #' lazy_Cobb_Douglas( #' utility = "x1^alpha*x2^(1-alpha)",  #' income = 80,  #' price = c(4, 3),   #' alpha = 0.64
